   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 56, 58.195868}", 
    "history" -> {"14.0", "14.3", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"quantum signal processing"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "QSPConvert[{\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, ...} -> parity] returns the full list of \
phases corresponding to the reduced phase vector {\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, ...} \
for a symmetric QSP of parity parity. QSPConvert[{\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, ..., \
\\[Phi]1, \\[Phi]0}] returns the reduced phase vector {\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, \
...} -> parity for a symmetric QSP of parity corresponding to the full \
symmetric phase vector {\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, ..., \\[Phi]1, \\[Phi]0}. \
QSPConvert[QSP[{\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, ...} -> parity, rest]] converts the \
symmetric quantum signal processing to the full-vector form QSP[{\\[Phi]0, \
\\[Phi]1, ..., \\[Phi]1, \\[Phi]0}, rest]. QSPConvert[{\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, \
..., \\[Phi]1, \\[Phi]0}, rest] converts the symmetric quantum signal \
processing in the general form with full phase vector to the reduced form \
QSPConvert[QSP[{\\[Phi]0, \\[Phi]1, ...} -> parity, rest]].", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "QSPConvert", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "QSPConvert", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/QSPConvert"}},
